               <msContents>
                  <summary>F<locus target="#1r">fols. 1r, </locus>-110v: Homiliary in Honor of the Monthly Feast of the Archangel Michael, 20th c Gov Scriptorium. <locus target="#17v">17v, </locus> mentions the owner, ወልደ ኢያሱስ, and the soul of his father, ወልደ ጊዮርጊስ. <locus target="#23v">23v, </locus> mentions another owner (?), ወልደ ሰንበት. F<locus target="#24v">24v, </locus> and passim mention the scribe, ወልደ ኢየሱስ. <locus target="#97v">97v</locus> gives his given name, ወልደ ኢየሱስ ኢያቄም, and also his late father, ወልደ ጊዮርጊስ. The illuminations appear to be authentic. </summary>
